PART III: THE CROWN DECISION (THE PIVOT)
Setting
The fire is burning low. The party has eaten, tended to wounds, and processed the individual weight of their personal arcs. Now, the political reality crashes back in.
Galmar Stone-Fist approaches the fire. He's cleaned some of the blood and dust from his armor, but he still looks like a man who just fought through a tomb full of the dead. He's carrying a wineskin and looks uncharacteristically hesitant.

The Request
Read Aloud: "Galmar stops at the edge of the firelight, just outside your circle. He doesn't sit. He stands there, his massive frame silhouetted against the camp behind him, and clears his throat.
'I need to ask you something.'
He looks at Kyboh, who is holding the Jagged Crown.
'The tomb is gone. Sealed forever. But tell me we didn't leave the prize in the dark.'"
GM Note: This is the moment. Galmar is asking, not demanding. He's vulnerable here—he wants the Crown desperately, but he's already offered them brotherhood. He's already treated them as equals. If they refuse him now, it will hurt more than any wound he took in the tomb.
Pacing: Let the players respond. Let them argue, discuss, feel the weight of this. This is the decision that defines their place in the Civil War.

