Appendix A: Advanced Davinia Mechanics (The Crown of the Pale Lady)
Following Davinia's extensive use of the Crown at Korvanjund, she has entered Tier 3: The Crossroads. The supernatural influence of Ismara Ice-Born is beginning to overwrite her mortal identity.
I. The Intuition Void (New Social Penalty)
The Penalty: Davinia can no longer instinctively intuit when an ally is physically hurt, even if they are downed or bleeding out on the battlefield.
The Audible Requirement: She cannot use helpful spells (Restoration, Wards) or the Help action to assist another character unless that character (or a conscious observer) specifically and audibly requests her aid.
The Narrative: Without a verbal command to "reinforce a failing unit," the Crown views trauma as a statistical inevitability of conflict. Davinia sees structural failure, not mortal suffering.
II. The Bi-Directional Resource Drain (The Soul Matrix)
The Crown has fused its energy channels into Davinia's respiratory and circulatory systems. This is now an Involuntary Transmutation Loop:
Loop A (Stamina Priority):
If Davinia's FP falls below 4, the Crown automatically drains 2 HP to replenish 4 FP.
Loop B (Physical Stability):
If Davinia's HP drops to 2 or less, the Crown drains 4 FP to restore 2 HP.
The Sensation: Liquid ice pumped directly into her veins. Her skin becomes unnaturally pale, her pulse slow and rhythmic, like a drum in a deep tomb.
III. Queen's Sight (The Architectural Gaze)
Davinia's connection to Greensight is severed. In its place, she has the vision of the Living Phylactery—viewing the world as structural stresses and geometric patterns.
New Ability: Structural Analysis
Action: Major Action
Effect: Analyze a target. Perceive flaws in armor or physiology.
