The Narrative Function: This ghoul serves as a reminder that Alfonso's work is self-sustaining. His creations seek him out across miles of wilderness, guided by Peryite's connection.
Ulag as Patient Zero
Ulag the Breaker's industrial physiology (Dragonplate armor bolted to his skeleton, Troll-mandible respirator, alchemical rig) makes him the perfect vessel for Alfonso's pathogen.
The Symbiosis: Rather than dying, Ulag's life-support rig preserves and nurtures the infection. He becomes Patient Zero for the Enhanced Scourge.
The Mechanical Effect: Ulag's respirator now vents clouds of Alfonso's infectious rot alongside his acrid green steam. Anyone engaging him in melee is exposed to the "Worthy Rival" strain.
Antoine's Reaction
When Ulag returns to Forelhost, Antoine will discover Alfonso's pathogen and view it as a "divine revelation." He will begin work on Forelhost Plague 2.0, a refined version designed to "re-order" Alfonso's chaotic necro-biology.
The Competitive Symbiosis: The two strains recognize each other as rival iterations of the same apocalyptic goal.
The Minion Hijacking: If Alfonso's ghouls are exposed to the 2.0 strain, Antoine's superior Guile allows him to override Alfonso's psychic control, turning the ghouls against their master.

Appendix C: Orion's Three-Way Pressure Cooker
The Brotherhood (Varon)
